@inherits Umbraco.Cms.Web.Common.Views.UmbracoViewPage
    <div class="using-panel">
        <h2>Using the Handbook</h2>

        <p>
            This handbook is organized into four main tabs on the left. Use them to navigate between welcome information, how-to instructions, the full set of policies, and support resources.
        </p>

        <h3>Understanding the Layout</h3>
    <dl class="using-layout-list">
        <dt>Tabs</dt>
        <dd>Located on the left-hand side for quick navigation.</dd>

        <dt>Search Bar</dt>
        <dd>Helps locate specific policies by keyword (coming soon).</dd>

        <dt>Policy Cards</dt>
        <dd>Display summaries with expandable full content.</dd>
    </dl>


        <h3>Selecting Your State</h3>
        <p>
            Some policies have state-specific variations. Use the dropdown menu labeled
            <strong>"Choose your work state"</strong> to select the appropriate state.
            If available, an additional section will appear under each policy with applicable details.
        </p>

        <h3>Tab Order & Navigation</h3>
        <p>
            You can use your keyboard to navigate tabs using the arrow keys. Each panel is fully accessible by screen readers, and skip logic ensures smooth transitions.
        </p>
    </div>
